What you need to know:

Kevin De Bruyne opened the scoring on 19 minutes for the runaway Premier League leaders, but Dortmund grabbed a vital away goal when Erling Haaland teed up Marco Reus to equalise six minutes from timeThe Algerian started a brilliant team move as De Bruyne, Foden and Mahrez exchanged passes before the Belgian tapped home from close rangeDe Bruyne was the creator again as his cross found Ilkay Gundogan at the back post and his cut-back was swept home by a relieved Foden